# Schemas

- Use **Zod** only for validation
- Schemas live in shared `schemas/` folder
- Integrate with Swagger for auto-generated docs
- **DTOs derived from root entity**: define a base entity schema, then build DTOs with `pick`, `partial`, `omit`, `extend`, etc.

```typescript
// schemas/user.schema.ts
import { z } from "zod";

/** Root entity schema - source of truth for all user DTOs */
export const userSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  name: z.string(),
  email: z.string().email(),
  createdAt: z.coerce.date(),
});

/** Create DTO - pick required fields from entity */
export const createUserSchema = userSchema.pick({ name: true, email: true });

/** Update DTO - partial of updatable fields */
export const updateUserSchema = userSchema.pick({ name: true, email: true }).partial();

/** Response DTO - omit internal/sensitive fields */
export const userResponseSchema = userSchema.omit({ createdAt: true });

/** DTO with extra computed fields - extend from pick */
export const userWithStatsSchema = userSchema.pick({ id: true, name: true }).extend({
  documentCount: z.number(),
});
```
